load ../restorable-context.maude

--- INV-1 coverage: a checkpoint at a quiescent point -- no inFlight -- reaches
--- a well-formed cut binding the CURRENT positions of all three planes --
--- transcript 5, instance 9, manifest 100.
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { checkpointReq(1) transcriptPlane(5) instancePlane(9) filePlane(100) }
  =>! { cut(1, 5, 9, 100) transcriptPlane(5) instancePlane(9) filePlane(100) } .

--- INV-3 + INV-4 coverage: a restore whose manifest hashes are ALL present
--- applies atomically -- all three planes move from the pre positions (0, 0, 0)
--- to the cut positions (5, 9, 100) in one step.
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { restoreReq(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71) blob(71)
    transcriptPlane(0) instancePlane(0) filePlane(0) }
  =>! { restored(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71) blob(71)
    transcriptPlane(5) instancePlane(9) filePlane(100) } .

--- INV-4 coverage (refuse path): a restore whose manifest requires content
--- hash 71 that the store does NOT hold is refused -- all three planes stay at
--- the pre positions (0, 0, 0).
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { restoreReq(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71)
    transcriptPlane(0) instancePlane(0) filePlane(0) }
  =>! { refused(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71)
    transcriptPlane(0) instancePlane(0) filePlane(0) } .

--- INV-2 bite (no-in-flight straddle): with an effect in flight, no reachable
--- state carries a cut -- the checkpoint guard bites. This is the wrapped-state
--- check: with a bare soup the checkpoint would rewrite a fragment with the
--- inFlight bound into none and this would find a solution.
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { inFlight(7) checkpointReq(1) transcriptPlane(5) instancePlane(9) filePlane(100) }
  =>* { cut(1, PP:Nat, NN:Nat, HH:Nat) RESIDUAL:Cfg } .

--- INV-3 bite (CRUX -- atomicity): even though the restore CAN apply -- blob 71
--- is present -- no reachable state is partially restored: the file plane at the
--- cut manifest (100) never coexists with the instance plane still at pre (0).
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { restoreReq(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71) blob(71)
    transcriptPlane(0) instancePlane(0) filePlane(0) }
  =>* { filePlane(100) instancePlane(0) RESIDUAL:Cfg } .

--- INV-3 bite (CRUX -- atomicity, second mismatch): the transcript plane at the
--- cut (5) never coexists with the file plane still at pre (0). Any 2-of-3
--- mismatch is unreachable -- the three planes move as one.
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { restoreReq(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71) blob(71)
    transcriptPlane(0) instancePlane(0) filePlane(0) }
  =>* { transcriptPlane(5) filePlane(0) RESIDUAL:Cfg } .

--- INV-4 bite (CRUX -- coherence): the manifest requires content hash 71 which
--- the store does NOT hold. No reachable applied-restore state exists -- the
--- file plane never moves to the cut manifest (100) and restored(1) never
--- appears. The "transcript remembers a file the store no longer has"
--- incoherence is unreachable.
search in RESTORABLE-CONTEXT :
  { restoreReq(1) cut(1, 5, 9, 100) requires(100, 71)
    transcriptPlane(0) instancePlane(0) filePlane(0) }
  =>* { restored(1) filePlane(100) RESIDUAL:Cfg } .

quit .
